<section class="content-1">
    <div class="content1-section">
        <h2>Orion</h2>
        <p>
            Orion is one of the most recognizable constellations, named for the mythological hunter in Greek myth. It is prominent in the winter sky and is visible from most of the world because it lies near the celestial equator. Key features include the three bright stars of <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=Orion">Orion’s Belt</a> and prominent stars like the red supergiant <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=Betelgeuse">Betelgeuse</a> and the blue supergiant <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=Rigel">Rigel</a>. The <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=Orion+Nebula">Orion Nebula</a>, a region of star formation, is also located in the constellation.
        </p>
