<section class="content-2">
    <div class="content2-section">
        <h2>Scorpio</h2>
        <p>
            Scorpio is a zodiac constellation located in the southern celestial hemisphere, named for the scorpion and known for its bright stars and distinct hook-like shape. It is most visible during the summer in the Northern Hemisphere and is characterized by the bright red supergiant star <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=Antares">Antares</a>, which is considered the “heart” of the scorpion.
        </p>
